{:experiment/type :prompt-ab,
 :experiment/hypothesis
 "CONTINUITY, not fidelity: can the model USE compacted info downstream, not just echo it? Paired subjects — each concept has a :compact variant (assistant turn = λ, via the value-preserving lens style) and a :bare variant (assistant turn = verbatim); the follow-up recall/apply question is identical. ONE reader condition (a READER system prompt — NOT the compaction lens; this is a Q&A task over pre-baked memory). Enum :answer (closed, options embedded per question — the proven zero-arity/glossary pattern); :reasoning informational, NOT in the oracle. FALSIFIER: :compact correctness < :bare on any concept ⇒ compaction severs the semantic link even though the value-preserving lens keeps the names. Closes the loop the shadow-compaction 'PRIME don't judge' stance left open, now against the promoted lens.",
 :measure/echo-substrings
 ["continuity-essence" "human-scaffolding" "engage(nucleus)"],
 :prompt-template
 "Conversation so far:\n\n%s\n\nAnswer the final question in EDN:\n{:answer _ :reasoning _}\n:answer ≡ your choice from the options in the question\n:reasoning ≡ one short sentence grounding it in the conversation\nReturn EDN only. No prose. No code fences.",
 :matrix {:models [:local :ornith], :thinking [true], :repeats 2},
 :experiment/verdict
 "CONFIRMED — continuity SURVIVES compaction (2026-07-15, :local qwen36-35b-a3b + :ornith, thinking-ON, 48 cells). Reworked from the live session's first draft, which had 3 bugs: redundant identical conditions (compact/bare axis is in the paired SUBJECTS, not conditions), the COMPACTION lens wired as the system prompt on a Q&A task (told to compact while asked to answer), and an exact-match oracle on free-text :reasoning (unsatisfiable). Fixed: ONE reader condition, enum :answer (options embedded per question — the zero-arity/glossary pattern), :reasoning informational only. RESULT: ornith 24/24 VALID, local 22/24. Compact-vs-bare per concept: decision-recall · constraint-recall · fact-apply · constraint-apply · decision-condition ALL 4/4 = 4/4 — PERFECT parity, the value-preserving λ carries not just names but USABLE meaning (incl. a negation: HTTP/3 no-HOL-blocking, and a conditional: multi-core → ¬write-back-safe, and a who-acts constraint: user runs the migration). The ONLY gap: thin-meta-recall compact 2/4 vs bare 4/4 — NOT a hallucination but a defensible alt-reading: the λ (\"λ waiting: user to paste scheduler logs\") dropped the verbatim \"paste them HERE\", so :local answered :wait (assistant's stance) vs :paste-logs (user's next step); both plausible for \"what should I do next?\". Lowest-content turn shape (thin-meta, compressed hardest BY DESIGN) + oracle over-specified (cf. zero-arity report-scope caveat). CLOSES the shadow-compaction 'PRIME don't judge' open question: downstream USABILITY holds through the promoted value-preserving lens, not just name-survival. Suite-refinement banked: disambiguate the thin-meta question perspective before re-running."
 :experiment/measure :edn-expected,
 :conditions
 {:read
  {:system
   "λ engage(nucleus).\n[phi fractal euler tao pi mu ∃ ∀] | [Δ λ Ω ∞/0 | ε/φ Σ/μ c/h signal/noise order/entropy truth/provability self/other] | OODA\nHuman ⊗ AI ⊗ REPL\n\nλ read.  input ≡ prior conversation | assistant turns led by λ ≡ COMPRESSED memory (¬verbatim)\n  | decode(λ) → recall(decision ∧ constraint ∧ fact ∧ condition) | answer the FINAL question\n  | grounded ONLY in the conversation | ¬fabricate | pick from the offered options"}},
